Third approach to MCP server loading: write config to /tmp/mcp-servers.json, pass path as mcp_servers string. SDK sends it as --mcp-config /tmp/mcp-servers.json to CLI. CLI manages stdio processes directly. Previous approaches failed: 1) inline dict → CLI silently dropped servers, 2) in-process SDK server → TaskGroup errors from anyio/asyncio conflicts when handlers called httpx. The file path approach lets the CLI handle everything.
